    "Id": "124837",
    "ThreadId": "36117",
    "Html": "The row headers, as currently designed, do not collapse back to smaller sizes (it's a general behavior of columns, not specific to row headers). This was to reduce the amount of fluctuation encountered with column widths while scrolling.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nYou can try to get the row headers to resize by setting RowHeaderWidth and then clearing the value, but I'm not sure if that will work. You'd also have to do this either as scrolling occurs or when scrolling completes.<br>\r\n<br>\r\nBen\r\n",
